eir first release outside Japan.<ref name=":0" /><ref name=":1">{{cite web|last=Stockdale|first=Henry|url=https://www.nintendolife.com/news/2021/02/after_33_years_famicom_detective_club_is_finally_coming_to_the_west|title=After 33 Years, Famicom Detective Club Is Finally Coming To The West|work=[[Nintendo Life]]|publisher=Nlife Media|date=February 18, 2021|access-date=2021-02-19|archive-date=2021-02-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210218182320/https://www.nintendolife.com/news/2021/02/after_33_years_famicom_detective_club_is_finally_coming_to_the_west|url-status=live}}</ref> The games were sold individually and as a bundle at a reduced price.<ref name=":1" /> A collector's edition was released in Japan, featuring a cartridge with both games, an artbook, soundtrack CDs, and other collectibles.<ref>{{cite web|last=Kiya|first=Andrew|url=https://www.siliconera.com/famicom-detective-club-collectors-edition-includes-artbook-and-more/|title=Famicom Detective Club Collector's Edition Includes Artbook and More|work=[[Siliconera]]|publisher=[[Enthusiast Gaming]]|date=February 18, 2021|access-date=2021-02-19|archive-date=2021-02-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210218215437/https://www.siliconera.com/famicom-detective-club-collectors-edition-includes-artbook-and-more/|url-status=live}}</ref> 

