The character Ayumi Tachibana starred in {{nihongo foot|''BS Tantei Club: Yuki ni Kieta Kako'',|BS探偵倶楽部 雪に消えた過去||{{lit}} ''BS Detective Club: Lost Memories in the Snow''|lead=yes|group=lower-alpha}} an adventure game released by Nintendo in 1997 for the [[Satellaview]], a [[satellite modem]] peripheral for the Super Famicom.<ref name="HG101BSDC:TPtDitS">{{cite web|last=Brink|first=Daniel|url=http://www.hardcoregaming101.net/bs-detective-club-the-past-that-disappeared-in-the-snow/|title=BS Detective Club: The Past that Disappeared in the Snow|publisher=Hardcore Gaming 101|date=May 23, 2021|access-date=2021-05-23|archive-date=2021-05-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210524012012/http://www.hardcoregaming101.net/bs-detective-club-the-past-that-disappeared-in-the-snow/|url-status=live}}</ref> It was broadcast in three chapters; the first from February 9–15, the second from February 16–22, and the last from February 23–March 1.<ref name="AVGv2">{{cite magazine|last=|first=|url=https://archive.org/stream/Adventure_Gameside_Vol.2#page/n1/mode/2up|title=ファミコン探偵倶楽部 消えた後継者; ファミコン探偵倶楽部Part II うしろに立つ少女; BS探偵倶楽部 雪に消えた過去|magazine=Adventure Gameside|volume=2|publisher=Micro Magazine|date=January 18, 2014|pages=1–34|lang=ja|isbn=978-4896374506}}</ref><ref name="HG101BSDC:TPtDitS" /> The player takes the role of Ayumi (voiced by [[Yūko Minaguchi]]) investigating a murder to prove the innocence of her mother.<ref name="AVGv2" /><ref name="HG101BSDC:TPtDitS" /> Ayumi later appeared as a collectible trophy in ''[[Super Smash Bros. Melee]]'' (2001),<ref>'''Trophy Description (Ayumi Tachibana, Famicom Detective Club Part II [Japan Only] ):''' "Ayumi's the heroine of the Detective Club games, which were made for the Disk System. In the first installment of the series, Ayumi solved the murder of one of her friends, and shortly thereafter, she opened her own investigative agency. Since those early days, she's proven to be a daring and peerless crime solver." (Nintendo, ''Super Smash Bros. Melee'' [NA version], 3 Dec 2001.)</ref> and according to ''[[Super Smash Bros.]]'' series director [[Masahiro Sakurai]], was at one point considered as a fighter for ''Melee''.<ref>{{cite web|last=Yusaki|first=Hiyo|url=https://www.nintendo.co.jp/n01/n64/software/nus_p_nalj/smash/flash/syukeiken/return551.html|title=アンケート投稿拳!! from Questionnaire: 発売後のアンケート集計拳!!|work=速報スマブラ拳!!|publisher=[[Nintendo]]|date=2001|page=51|access-date=2021-02-19|language=ja|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201215083820/https://www.nintendo.co.jp/n01/n64/software/nus_p_nalj/smash/flash/syukeiken/return551.html|archive-date=2020-12-15|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite AV media|author1=Sugita, Tomokazu|author-link1=Tomokazu Sugita|author2=Ito, Kenji|date=19 March 2015|title=杉田智和＆伊藤賢治！大乱闘スマッシュブラザーズ 特別ゲーム実況|trans-title=Tomokazu Sugita & Kenji Ito! Super Smash Bros. Special Game Live|medium=[[Niconico]]|language=ja|url=https://live2.nicovideo.jp/watch/lv213419510|access-date=2021-02-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210219161404/https://live2.nicovideo.jp/watch/lv213419510|archive-date=2021-02-19|url-status=live|time=1h15m57s|location=Japan|publisher=[[Dwango (company)|Dwango]]}}</ref> In a 2021 interview, [[Mages (company)|Mages]] director Makoto Asada expressed interest in developing a new ''Famicom Detective Club'' entry.<ref name="Fam">{{cite magazine|last=Saiton|first=Lip|url=https://www.famitsu.com/news/202106/12223092.html|title=Switch『ファミコン探偵倶楽部』インタビュー。企画の発端から開発中のエピソードを少年探偵ばりに聞く【ネタバレあり】|magazine=[[Famitsu]]|publisher=Kadokawa Game Linkage|date=June 12, 2021|access-date=2021-06-12|lang=ja}}</ref>

